// =============================================================================
// core/control/mod.vr — Stdlib surface for control-flow primitives
// =============================================================================
// Layer: Standard Library / Control
// =============================================================================
//
// Higher-order control-flow primitives that go beyond plain
// `return` / `break` / `continue`:
//
//   * `continuation.vr` — Delimited continuations (`shift` / `reset`,
//     Danvy-Filinski 1990). First-class capture of "the rest of the
//     computation up to a marked boundary". Foundation for
//     user-space coroutines, generator-style iteration,
//     non-deterministic search via `core.action.monads.nondeterm`,
//     and effect-handler-style composition without baking effect
//     types into the language.
//
// Future additions (V1.5): undelimited `call/cc`, exception-style
// non-local jump primitives, prompt-based effect handlers.
// =============================================================================

module core.control;

public module continuation;
